Jenni Evans, News24(SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Police have arrested a man for murder in Germiston after the bodies of two small children were found in a disused building, police spokesperson Colonel Noxolo Kweza said on Tuesday.The girl and the boy - both aged eight - were reported missing on Sunday, said Kweza.With the help of the community, their bodies were found in a disused building on Monday afternoon.Kweza said a 40-year-old man was arrested and would face charges of murder.Further details of their disappearance, or how they died, were not immediately available.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.